A 39-year-old man, Imoleayo Benson, on Friday appeared before an Ikorodu Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State for allegedly stealing 24 MTN backup batteries worth N19.2 million. Benson, whose address was not provided, is facing a two-count charge bordering on conspiracy and felony to wit stealing. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. ALSO READ: FUOYE investigates attack on Fayemi’s wife The prosecutor, Sgt. John Iberedem told the court that the defendant committed the offences on July 13, at 12 a.m., at Devs Cartola Ltd MTN mask, inside Benson Estate, Ikorodu. Local singer arrested for allegedly criticising Ganduje… Yam festival: Angry youths on rampage over refusal of… Obasanjo, Anyaoku, Sanwo-Olu, others task Africa leaders on… Gov Bello unveils Free Healthcare Initiative in Kogi State Iberedem said that the defendant stole 24 backup batteries belonging to MTN Nigeria Communications PLC valued at N29.2 million. He said that the offences contravened Sections 314 and 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015 (Revised). The chief magistrate, Mrs F.A. Azeez, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N800,000 with two sureties in like sum. Azeez said that one of the sureties must have a landed property, be a blood relation of the defendant, show evidence of LASTRA registration and must be gainfully employed. She adjourned the case until Nov. 11, for mention. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
